-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/aymris-completes-u-s-plant-to-turn-sugar-into-chemicals-diesel.html
(Corrects company spelling in headline.)  Amyris Inc. (AMRS) , a biotechnology company
that converts sugarcane syrup into a hydrocarbon used to make
specialty chemicals and  diesel fuel , completed its first U.S.
production facility.  The plant is at a Decatur, Illinois, facility owned by Tate
& Lyle Ingredients Americas Inc., Emeryville, California-based
Amyris said today in a statement. Joel Velasco, Amyrisâ€™ senior
vice president of external relations, would not say how much of
the hydrocarbon, farnesene, it can produce.  Amyris also produces farnesene at facilities owned by
Biomin do Brasil Nutricao Animal Ltda. in Piracicaba, Brazil,
and Antibioticos SA in Leon, Spain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
